BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa al-Buhayri in London; from the "Good Day" </F>
column] 
  [Text] Millionaire Usamah Bin-Ladin, the primary source of 
financing for terrorist groups in Egypt and the Arab world, has 
requested political asylum in Holland. 
  Bin-Ladin, whose Saudi nationality has been withdrawn, 
manages his terrorist activities from Holland. He left Sudan 
after bombs were thrown at his home recently. 
  Bin-Ladin currently distributes leaflets opposed to Arab 
governments and regimes. 

